      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/79/1477",
      "text": [
        " اَلْمُسَافِرِ إِلَى مَكَّةَ وَ غَيْرِهَا هَلْ عَلَيْهِ صَلاَةُ اَلْعِيدَيْنِ اَلْفِطْرِ وَ اَلْأَضْحَى قَالَ «نَعَمْ إِلاَّ بِمِنًى يَوْمَ اَلنَّحْرِ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.1477 - Sa'd ibn Sa'd narrated from al-Ridha (as) regarding a traveler to Mecca or elsewhere, asking if the traveler is obligated to perform the Eid prayers (Eid al-Fitr and Eid al-Adha).\nHe (Imam (as)) said: \"Yes, except in Mina on the Day of Sacrifice (Eid al-Adha).\""
        ]
      }
    },
